Sure thing! Here's a basic example script that collects user interaction data and sends it to a server for analysis. Please note that this script should only be used for improving the user experience and not for any malicious purposes.

```javascript
// Collect user interaction data
const userData = [];
document.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
  const interactionData = {
    timestamp: Date.now(),
    eventType: event.type,
    eventData: event.target.outerHTML,
  };
  userData.push(interactionData);
});

// Send user interaction data to server for analysis
async function sendData() {
  try {
    const response = await fetch('/data-collection', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
      },
      body: JSON.stringify(userData),
    });
    const result = await response.json();
    console.log(result);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error sending data:', error);
  }
}

// Set up interval to send data periodically
setInterval(sendData, 60000); // Send data every 1 minute

// Initialize data sending
sendData();
```

Please note that this is a very basic example, and you should adjust it according to your specific requirements.
